A reaction is spontaneous when the equilibrium constant \( K_{eq} > 1 \), indicating more products than reactants at equilibrium. While \(\Delta G^\circ < 0\) (not listed) is the definitive criterion, \( K_{eq} > 1 \) directly implies spontaneity under standard conditions. Other options (e.g., \(\Delta H^\circ > 0\) or \(\Delta G^\circ > 0\)) suggest non-spontaneity.
